## ğŸ“˜ DP-700 â€“ Implement & Manage an Analytics Solution  
### Design & Implement Schedules and Event-Based Triggers (Microsoft Fabric)

---

## 1ï¸âƒ£ Trigger Types in Microsoft Fabric

### ğŸ” Schedule Trigger

**What it does**
- Runs a pipeline at a fixed time or recurrence  
- Uses **UTC time only**

**Best for**
- Daily / weekly batch jobs  
- Predictable ingestion windows  

**Key properties**
- Start time (UTC)  
- Recurrence (minute / hour / day / week)  
- Interval (e.g., every 1 day)

**Limitations**
- Runs even when no new data exists  
- No state tracking  
- Can cause unnecessary compute cost  

ğŸ“Œ **Exam signal**  
â€œRun every day at 02:00â€ â†’ **Schedule trigger**

---

### âš¡ Event-Based Trigger

**What it does**
- Starts a pipeline when a file is created  
- Uses **Azure Event Grid**

**Best for**
- Near real-time ingestion  
- Sporadic or unpredictable data arrival  

**Key requirements**
- Storage account supports Event Grid  
- Permissions to create event subscriptions  
- Triggered mainly on **file creation** events  

**Advantages**
- Cost-efficient  
- No polling  
- Faster ingestion  

**Limitations**
- No exactly-once guarantee  
- File updates may NOT trigger  
- One trigger per storage location  

ğŸ“Œ **Exam signal**  
â€œWhen a new file arrivesâ€ â†’ **Event-based trigger**

---

### â± Tumbling Window Trigger

**What it does**
- Divides time into fixed, non-overlapping windows  
- Tracks state per window  

**Best for**
- Exactly-once processing  
- Late-arriving data  
- Retry-safe pipelines  

**Key features**
- Window size (e.g., 1 hour)  
- Offset  
- Retry policies  
- Watermark support  

**Why it matters**
- Ensures each time slice is processed once and only once  

ğŸ“Œ **Exam signal**  
â€œExactly onceâ€, â€œhourly slicesâ€, â€œlate dataâ€ â†’ **Tumbling window**

---

## 2ï¸âƒ£ Trigger Configuration Scope

| Item               | Scope     |
|--------------------|-----------|
| Pipelines          | Workspace |
| Triggers           | Workspace |
| Lakehouse          | Workspace |
| Notebook execution | Workspace |
| Domain             | Governance only |

ğŸ“Œ **Exam trap**  
Triggers are NOT tenant-level and NOT notebook-level

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ Key Configuration Settings to Remember

### Schedule Triggers
- Time zone: **UTC only**  
- Start time is mandatory  
- Recurrence â‰  interval  

### Event-Based Triggers
- Requires Event Grid  
- Needs permissions  
- Reacts to file creation  
- Cannot aggregate multiple storage accounts  

### Tumbling Window Triggers
- Window size  
- Start time  
- Retry policy  
- State management enabled  

